cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is about using machine learning to extract clinical concepts from text for document-level coding. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning for text analysis. The paper also discusses using extracted concepts as features and labels, which suggests a focus on machine learning and data representation, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely second category. The paper also mentions information retrieval and domain ontologies, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with clinical data, which could make cs.CY (Computers and Society) a possible category as well.
